# agent-store
- label: agent-store builds a Rust CLI binary named agent-store that exits 0 for --help and prints usage, while bare invocation without a subcommand prints an error plus usage to stderr and exits 2
  id: 28o
  command: sh -c 'tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cargo run --quiet -- --help > $tmp/agent-store-help-28o.txt && grep -Fq "Usage: agent-store" $tmp/agent-store-help-28o.txt && set +e; cargo run --quiet -- >$tmp/agent-store-bare-28o.out 2>$tmp/agent-store-bare-28o.err; status=$?; set -e; test "$status" -eq 2 && test ! -s $tmp/agent-store-bare-28o.out && grep -Fq "error: missing command" $tmp/agent-store-bare-28o.err && grep -Fq "Usage: agent-store" $tmp/agent-store-bare-28o.err'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store has separate internal boundaries for CLI argument parsing, command execution, persistence access, and user-facing text/JSON output formatting
  id: 1gb
  tags: [implemented]

# CLI

## records
- label: agent-store create <kind> key=value... creates a Record, stores <kind> as its queryable kind, stores each key=value Field, and prints the Record ID
  id: b98
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-b98" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >$tmp/agent-store-create-b98-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-b98" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create task title=Write status=open); printf "%s\n" "$id" | grep -Eq "^[a-z0-9]{6,8}$"; out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-b98" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id"); test "$out" = "$id task status=open title=Write"'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find <Query> accepts either one quoted query argument or multiple unquoted arguments joined with spaces; it supports kind=<value>, Field = and != comparisons joined by and, prints matching Records in the default record format, and lists every Record when invoked without a Query
  id: m2b
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh find_filters_records
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store rm <ID> resolves an unambiguous short Record ID, hard-deletes that Record, prints Removed <resolved-id>, and exits non-zero with a not-found message when no Record matches
  id: 15k
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-15k" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >$tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-15k" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create task title=DeleteMe status=open); prefix=$(printf "%s" "$id" | cut -c1-4); out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-15k" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- rm "$prefix"); test "$out" = "Removed $id"; if CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-15k" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id" >$tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-get.out 2>$tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-get.err; then exit 1; fi; grep -Fq "was not found" $tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-get.err; if CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-15k" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- rm "$id" >$tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-again.out 2>$tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-again.err; then exit 1; fi; grep -Fq "was not found" $tmp/agent-store-rm-15k-again.err'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store get <ID> prints the Record with that short ID in the default record output format
  id: rzr
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-rzr" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >$tmp/agent-store-get-rzr-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-rzr" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create decision choice=sqlite area=persistence); out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-rzr" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id"); test "$out" = "$id decision area=persistence choice=sqlite"'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store set <ID> key=value... resolves an unambiguous short Record ID, atomically updates supplied Fields on the existing Record, accepts empty and null values, leaves unspecified Fields unchanged, and prints Updated <resolved-id>
  id: 1b1
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh set_updates_fields
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store unset <ID> key... resolves an unambiguous short Record ID, atomically removes the supplied Fields from the existing Record, leaves other Fields unchanged, keeps the Record, and prints Updated <resolved-id>
  id: d77
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh unset_removes_fields
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find <Query> accepts single- or double-quoted comparison values that may contain spaces and operator characters, treats backslash inside quotes as an escape for the next character, and matches k='' and k!='' against Fields stored as the empty string
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh query_quoted_values
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find and ls without a Query list every stored Record in the default record format and return the same records object shape under --json
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh find_lists_all_records
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store create and set reject with exit code 2 and an error: message an empty kind, any kind or field name containing whitespace, control characters, quotes, or =, reject the reserved field names kind, id, and not, and reject not as a kind, while field values stay unrestricted and previously valid unicode/dot/dash/underscore identifiers keep working
  id: ol0
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh identifier_validation_rejects_unsafe_names
  tags: [implemented]
- label: get and find --json include created_at and updated_at as UTC RFC3339 strings on every record object; create sets both, set and unset bump updated_at only when they change data, and records from pre-existing stores still print valid timestamps
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && id=$(agent-store create note k=v) && agent-store get $id --json | jq -e ".record.created_at and .record.updated_at" && sleep 1 && agent-store set $id k=w >/dev/null && test "$(agent-store get $id --json | jq -r .record.created_at)" != "$(agent-store get $id --json | jq -r .record.updated_at)"
  tags: [implemented]
- label: find Queries can compare the built-in created_at and updated_at timestamps with the existing comparison operators alongside Field predicates
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store create note k=v >/dev/null && test "$(agent-store find "created_at>2020-01-01" --json | jq ".records | length")" = 1 && test "$(agent-store find "created_at>2999-01-01" --json | jq ".records | length")" = 0
  tags: [implemented]
- label: find and ls accept --sort <field> including created_at/updated_at/kind/id and Field names, --desc to reverse, --limit N to cap printed results, and --count to print the total match count ignoring --limit, composing with Queries in plain and --json output
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store create t n=2 >/dev/null && agent-store create t n=1 >/dev/null && agent-store create t n=3 >/dev/null && test "$(agent-store find --sort n --json | jq -r ".records[0].fields.n")" = 1 && test "$(agent-store find --sort n --desc --limit 1 --json | jq -r ".records[0].fields.n")" = 3 && test "$(agent-store find --count)" = 3 && test "$(agent-store find --limit 1 --count)" = 3 && test "$(agent-store find --limit 1 --count --json | jq -r .count)" = 3
  tags: [implemented]
- label: find and ls without --sort list Records in creation order oldest first instead of ID order
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && a=$(agent-store create t seq=first) && sleep 1.1 && b=$(agent-store create t seq=second) && test "$(agent-store find --json | jq -r ".records[0].id")" = "$a"
  tags: [implemented]
- label: find Queries support ~= as a case-insensitive substring comparison on kind and Field values, composing with and/or/not and parentheses, and find --help plus the installed skill query docs document the ~= operator
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store create task title="Fix Login Page" >/dev/null && agent-store create task title="update docs" >/dev/null && test "$(agent-store find "title~='login'" --json | jq ".records | length")" = 1 && test "$(agent-store find "title~=LOGIN" --json | jq ".records | length")" = 1 && test "$(agent-store find "not title~=login" --json | jq ".records | length")" = 1 && agent-store find --help | grep -q "~=" 
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store create --stdin reads JSONL from stdin (one {"kind":...,"fields":{...}} object per line, the find --json record shape, ignoring extra keys like id and timestamps so exports round-trip), creates one Record per line firing Hooks per record, prints each created ID on its own line (a {"records":[...]} envelope under --json), and fails with a non-zero exit and no partial silent skip on an invalid line
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && printf "%s\n%s\n" "{\"kind\":\"task\",\"fields\":{\"title\":\"a\"}}" "{\"kind\":\"task\",\"fields\":{\"title\":\"b\"}}" | agent-store create --stdin | wc -l | grep -qx 2 && agent-store find --json | jq ".records" > exp.json && agent-store find --json | jq -c ".records[]" | (mkdir d2 && cd d2 && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store create --stdin >/dev/null && test "$(agent-store find --count)" = 2) && ! echo "not json" | agent-store create --stdin 2>/dev/null
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store set with values the Record already holds and unset of Fields it does not have leave updated_at untouched, print Unchanged <ID> (status unchanged under --json), and exit 0, while a mutation with at least one real change still prints Updated <ID> and bumps updated_at
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh set_noop_leaves_updated_at
  tags: [implemented]

## output
- label: agent-store prints Records one per line as <id> <kind> key=value... with stable field ordering and shell-quoted values when needed
  id: zaj
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-zaj" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >$tmp/agent-store-output-zaj-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-zaj" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create note title="hello world" status=open empty=); out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-zaj" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id"); test "$out" = "$id note empty='\'''\'' status=open title='\''hello world'\''"'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init, create/cr, get, find/ls, set, unset, and rm accept --json and print valid structured JSON with record objects or mutation/summary objects instead of prose
  id: jjy
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh json_output
  tags: [implemented]
- label: under --json, runtime errors print a one-line {"error":"<message>"} object on stderr with the same message text and exit codes as plain mode (1 runtime, 2 invalid query) and nothing on stdout, while usage errors from argument parsing stay plain text
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh json_error_envelope
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store exits quietly with code 141 and no panic or stderr output when stdout's reader closes early during find or --json get output
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh broken_pipe_exits_quietly
  tags: [implemented]
- label: compact text output of get and find omits timestamps by default and appends created_at and updated_at when --timestamps is passed
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && id=$(agent-store create note k=v) && ! agent-store get $id | grep -q created_at && agent-store get $id --timestamps | grep -q created_at=
  tags: [implemented]

## init
- label: agent-store init creates .agent-store/ in the current directory and adds a .agent-store/ ignore rule to .gitignore
  id: k6a
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-k6a" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >$tmp/agent-store-init-k6a.out; test -d .agent-store; grep -Fxq ".agent-store/" .gitignore'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init installs the agent-store, agent-store-patterns, and agent-store-pipelines builtin skills as SKILL.md files under both .agents/skills and .claude/skills
  id: 4je
  command: sh -c "set -eu; repo=\$PWD; tmp=\$(mktemp -d); cd \"\$tmp\"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-4je\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >\$tmp/agent-store-init-4je.out; for root in .agents/skills .claude/skills; do for skill in agent-store agent-store-patterns agent-store-pipelines; do test -f \"\$root/\$skill/SKILL.md\"; grep -Fq \"name: \$skill\" \"\$root/\$skill/SKILL.md\"; done; done; rm -rf \"\$tmp\""
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init appends a managed usage block to existing AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md files while preserving their existing content
  id: ciy
  command: sh -c "set -eu; repo=\$PWD; tmp=\$(mktemp -d); cd \"\$tmp\"; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > AGENTS.md; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > CLAUDE.md; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-ciy\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >\$tmp/agent-store-init-ciy.out; for doc in AGENTS.md CLAUDE.md; do grep -Fq \"user-authored line\" \"\$doc\"; grep -Fq \"<!-- agent-store:start -->\" \"\$doc\"; grep -Fq \"agent-store init\" \"\$doc\"; grep -Fq \"<!-- agent-store:end -->\" \"\$doc\"; done; rm -rf \"\$tmp\""
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init can be run repeatedly without duplicating managed instruction blocks or overwriting pre-existing skill files, and repeat runs report Already initialized (exit 0, JSON status already-initialized) instead of Initialized
  id: vpz
  command: sh -c "set -eu; repo=\$PWD; tmp=\$(mktemp -d); cd \"\$tmp\"; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > AGENTS.md; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > CLAUDE.md; mkdir -p .agents/skills/agent-store .claude/skills/agent-store; printf \"custom agent skill\\n\" > .agents/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; printf \"custom claude skill\\n\" > .claude/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-vpz\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >\$tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-1.out; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-vpz\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >\$tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-2.out; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-vpz\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- --json init >\$tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-3.out; grep -Fxq \"Initialized .agent-store/\" \$tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-1.out; grep -Fxq \"Already initialized .agent-store/\" \$tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-2.out; grep -Fq \"\\\"status\\\":\\\"already-initialized\\\"\" \$tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-3.out; test \"\$(grep -Fc \"<!-- agent-store:start -->\" AGENTS.md)\" -eq 1; test \"\$(grep -Fc \"<!-- agent-store:start -->\" CLAUDE.md)\" -eq 1; test \"\$(grep -Fc \".agent-store/\" .gitignore)\" -eq 1; grep -Fxq \"custom agent skill\" .agents/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; grep -Fxq \"custom claude skill\" .claude/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; rm -rf \"\$tmp\""
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init output enumerates what it did — installed skill paths, instruction blocks added or already present per file, and a create-and-re-run hint when no AGENTS.md or CLAUDE.md exists — in both text and --json modes
  id: iou
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh init_output_summary
  tags: [implemented]
- label: every command except init fails with exit code 1 and a no agent-store found; run 'agent-store init' first stderr message when no .agent-store/ exists in the current directory or any ancestor, creates no files or directories as a side effect, and works normally after agent-store init
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh uninitialized_store_errors
  tags: [implemented]

