## hooks
- label: agent-store hook add <event> [<Query>] -- <bash command> stores a Hook for a supported Store Event name with a generated Hook ID, optional Query text, and Bash command, then prints the Hook ID
  id: 1me
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_add_stores_metadata
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store hook ls prints Hooks one per line as <id> <event> [query=<shell-quoted-query>] -- <shell-quoted-command>, in registration order (oldest Hook first), matching Hook execution order
  id: pn0
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_ls_deterministic
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store hook rm <ID> resolves an unambiguous short Hook ID, deletes that Hook, prints Removed <resolved-id>, and exits non-zero with a not-found message when no Hook matches
  id: nih
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_rm_deletes_metadata
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store hook add, hook ls, and hook rm accept --json and print structured JSON consistent with record mutation output ({"status":"added","hook":{...}}, {"hooks":[...]}, and {"status":"removed","hook":{...}} with id, event, query-or-null, and command per Hook) while plain output stays unchanged
  id: hkj
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_json_output
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store hook runs lists persisted Hook Runs newest first (default limit 20, --limit N override) as one summary line per run with run id, timestamp, Hook ID, event, Record ID, and exit status without dumping captures; hook runs <run-id> prints one run's full detail including captured stdout and stderr; --json prints structured {"hook_runs":[...]} and {"hook_run":{...}} objects with captures; an empty store exits 0 with a friendly plain message or an empty JSON list; hook --help mentions runs
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_runs_command
  tags: [implemented]

## context
- label: agent-store ctx prints a compact deterministic Quick Context summary of aggregates plus a Recent records section with Record IDs, kinds, and truncated Field values, without dumping full untruncated Field values
  id: wpx
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_context.sh ctx_summary_default
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store context is a readable alias for ctx with identical behavior and byte-for-byte identical output
  id: i3l
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_context.sh context_alias_matches_ctx
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store --json ctx prints one valid JSON object mirroring the plain Quick Context summary with record_count, records_by_kind, fields_by_kind, status_counts_by_kind, date_windows_by_kind, link_count, links_by_relation, hook_count, latest_activity_at, and recent_records (IDs, kinds, truncated fields)
  id: cxj
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_context.sh ctx_json_summary
  tags: [implemented]
- label: ctx and ctx --json include a Recent records section listing the most recently updated Records with their IDs, kinds, and truncated Field values, while total ctx output stays within the 8192-byte cap even when records hold large values
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store create handoff summary="Refactor auth module next; JWT rotation is half-done" >/dev/null && big=$(head -c 20000 /dev/zero | tr "\\0" "x") && agent-store create blob data="$big" >/dev/null && agent-store ctx | grep -qi "recent" && agent-store ctx | grep -q "Refactor auth module" && test "$(agent-store ctx | wc -c)" -le 8192 && agent-store ctx --json | jq -e ".recent_records | length >= 1" >/dev/null && test "$(agent-store ctx --json | wc -c)" -le 8192
  tags: [implemented]

## links
- label: agent-store link <from> <rel> <to> resolves unambiguous short Record IDs, idempotently creates one directional Link, prints Linked <from-id> <rel> <to-id>, and does not duplicate the Link when repeated
  id: q59
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh link_adds_idempotently
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store unlink <from> <rel> <to> resolves unambiguous short Record IDs, removes that directional Link, and prints Unlinked <from-id> <rel> <to-id>; when no such Link exists it exits non-zero with an error no such link message on stderr, prints nothing on stdout (plain and --json), fires no Hooks, and records no Store Event or Hook Run
  id: 80k
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh unlink_removes_and_missing_fails
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store links <ID> resolves an unambiguous short Record ID and prints outgoing Links as out <rel> <to-id> lines followed by incoming Links as in <rel> <from-id> lines, each sorted by relation and peer Record ID
  id: cav
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh links_lists_deterministically
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store find <Query> treats link.out=<rel> and link.in=<rel> as direction-plus-relation Link predicates, treats link.out.<rel>=<record-id> and link.in.<rel>=<record-id> as direction-plus-relation-plus-peer Record ID Link predicates, and composes those predicates with the existing boolean Query language
  id: l7a
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh find_filters_links
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store link <from> <rel> <to> rejects linking a Record to itself, including via distinct short prefixes resolving to the same Record: it exits non-zero with error cannot link a record to itself (<id>) on stderr (plain and --json envelope), prints nothing on stdout, creates no Link, fires no Hooks, and records no Store Event
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh self_link_rejected
  tags: [implemented]

## help
- label: agent-store documented subcommands, aliases, and hook subcommands treat -h and --help as read-only help: each exits 0, prints command-specific usage, and does not create, update, delete, link, unlink, or run Hooks
  id: x3h
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_help.sh subcommand_help_is_read_only
  tags: [implemented]
- label: find --help documents --sort, --desc, --limit, --count, and --timestamps, and the builtin agent-store skill doc installed by init describes timestamps and the new find flags
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && agent-store find --help | grep -q -- --sort && agent-store find --help | grep -q -- --count && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && grep -q -- --sort .agents/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md
  tags: [implemented]
- label: hook --help documents the AGENT_STORE_ID, AGENT_STORE_KIND, and AGENT_STORE_EVENT environment variables passed to Hook commands, and the installed agent-store skill docs describe them
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store hook --help | grep -q AGENT_STORE_ID && agent-store hook --help | grep -q AGENT_STORE_EVENT && agent-store init >/dev/null && grep -rq AGENT_STORE_ID .agents/skills/agent-store/
  tags: [implemented]

# domain
- label: a Store is a project-local SQLite-backed database under .agent-store
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh store_is_project_local
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Record is a stored item with a generated 6-8 character random hash ID, a kind, and arbitrary named Fields
  id: 6hu
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh json_output
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Field is a key-value attribute attached to a Record; Field names and kinds exclude whitespace, control characters, quotes, and '=', 'kind' and 'id' are reserved names, 'not' is reserved as a kind and field name, and values are unrestricted
  id: ypj
