- label: Matching Hooks for plain create, set, unset, rm, link, and unlink mutations run sequentially in registration order (oldest Hook first, even when Hook IDs sort differently) after the triggering mutation commits; earlier-registered successful Hook Runs persist, the first failing or timed-out Hook Run persists and makes the CLI exit non-zero with the normal mutation output on stdout and useful stderr, later-registered matching Hooks do not run, the Store mutation remains committed, and each Bash command starts in the project root with the default 30-second timeout that hook and hook add help document
  id: 4as
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo test --quiet --test hook_stress hooks_run_sequentially_from_project_root_with_timeout -- --list --ignored | grep -qx "hooks_run_sequentially_from_project_root_with_timeout: test" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "pwd >> order" >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "echo second >> order" >/dev/null && agent-store create note k=v >/dev/null && test "$(sed -n 1p order)" = "$d" && test "$(sed -n 2p order)" = second && agent-store hook --help | grep -q "30-second"
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Bash commands for create, set, unset, and rm receive AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, and AGENT_STORE_KIND matching the affected Record snapshot
