- label: A Hook timeout or non-zero exit makes the triggering CLI command exit non-zero, reports that the Store mutation already committed, and leaves the committed Record and Hook Run persisted
  id: fgg
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo test --quiet --test hook_stress hook_failure_or_timeout_reports_committed_mutation -- --list --ignored | grep -qx "hook_failure_or_timeout_reports_committed_mutation: test" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "exit 1" >/dev/null && ! agent-store create note k=v >out 2>err && test -s out && grep -q "already committed" err && test "$(agent-store find --count)" = 1 && test "$(agent-store hook runs --json | jq ".hook_runs | length")" = 1
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook stdout and stderr capture are capped at 8192 bytes each, cap values are documented in command help, and representative plain and JSON mutations whose failing or timed-out Hook emits substantial or non-UTF-8 output do not hang or panic, persist diagnosable Hook Run output, report useful committed-failure stderr, and keep the normal mutation output on stdout
  id: lc1
  command: repo=$PWD && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo build --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" && export PATH="$repo/target/facts-bin/debug:$PATH" && CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-bin" cargo test --quiet --test hook_stress hook_output_capture_caps_and_help -- --list --ignored | grep -qx "hook_output_capture_caps_and_help: test" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store hook runs --help | grep -q 8192 && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "yes x | head -c 100000 >&2; exit 1" >/dev/null && ! timeout 90 agent-store create note k=v 2>err && grep -q "already committed" err && test "$(agent-store hook runs --json | jq -r ".hook_runs[0].stderr | length <= 8192")" = true
  tags: [implemented]
